932494208488},"country":"Türkiye"},"builtYear":2023,"architect":"FATMA KISAR VİKİNG YACHT DESİGN FETHİYE","interiorDesigner":"MEAN DESİGN İSTANBUL","topSpeed":12,"cruiseSpeed":10,"cabinLayout":[{"label":"Master cabin","value":"1"},{"label":"Double Cabins","value":"3"},{"label":"Twin Cabins","value":"1"}],"cabins":5,"bathrooms":5,"length":44,"beam":9.5,"draft":3.3,"hullType":"","hullConstruction":"wood","tonnage":335,"superStructure":[],"engines":"2 x 850Hp MAN","amenities":[{"label":"Salon TV","quantity":1},{"label":"Generator","quantity":1},{"label":"Children Allowed","quantity":1},{"label":"Ice Maker","quantity":1},{"label":"Salon Stereo","quantity":1},{"label":"Hairdryers","quantity":1},{"label":"Inverter","quantity":1},{"label":"Sat TV","quantity":1},{"label":"BBQ","quantity":1},{"label":"iPod/Device Hookups","quantity":1},{"label":"Deck shower","quantity":1},{"label":"Dine In","quantity":1},{"label":"Onboard WIFI","quantity":1},{"label":"Sat TV","quantity":1},{"label":"Air Conditioning","quantity":1}],"toys":[{"label":"Jet Skis","quantity":"2"},{"label":"Ringo"},{"label":"Kayak"},{"label":"Water ski (adults and children)"},{"label":"Wakeboard"},{"label":"Seabob"},{"label":"Waydoo efoil eletric"},{"label":"SUP"},{"label":"Big mable"}],"entertainment":["Onboard WIFI","Salon TV","Salon Stereo","Sat TV","Tv in cabins",""],"tenders":["Service tender Northstar 4.80 with 100hp Honda outboard","Northstar Orion 7 mt with 250hp Honda outboard"]},"crew":[{"name":"Kamil Yesim","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::7819143053::vessel::77945888-486c-11ee-a45f-fdfff6163a60::assets::1bcc6760-295e-11ef-bff7-9d94981faba8.jpeg/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"Birth: 05.03.1983 in Köycegiz\nPrevious work experience in brief: Kamil started sailing at the age of 16 as a sailor. In the same year, he obtained his license and started working on the charter yacht Balina. After completing his military duty, he continued to work on the same yacht for 4 years. In 2007, he started to work as a captain on the charter boat, Nurlum. Then he became captain on North Wind, following the construction in the shipyard from the first day.\nHe has been working in the yachting industry for 24 years.\nLanguages Known: Turkish (Native) - English (A2)\nHobbies/ interests: Repair, sailing."},{"name":"Ayatullah Deniz","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::7819143053::vessel::77945888-486c-11ee-a45f-fdfff6163a60::assets::4d879310-295e-11ef-bff7-9d94981faba8.jpeg/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"Birth: 30/03/1980 in Diyarbakir\nPrevious work experiences in brief: Ayatullah started working in the kitchen as soon as he graduated from high school. He has worked in many different positions in many restaurants in Istanbul, Bodrum and Cyprus for nearly 30 years.  \nHe started working in the yachting business in 2018 on yacht Casa dell’Arte, then moved  to Queen of Makri, before joining the North Wind crew.\nHonor mention at 2024 Tyba Chef Competition.\nHobbies/ interests: Culinary arts, Traditional and World Cuisine"},{"name":"Aysegul Simsek","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::7819143053::vessel::77945888-486c-11ee-a45f-fdfff6163a60::assets::869e2330-295e-11ef-bff7-9d94981faba8.jpeg/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"Birth: 15.01.1981 in Istanbul\nEducation: Istanbul Maltepe Commercial Vocational High School\nPrevious Work Experiences in Brief: Ayşegül started her bank internship in 1998 and worked at Koçbank until 2001. Between 2005 and 2008, she worked as an assistant for Kiptaş Dragos Construction Site. After maternity she moved to Fethiye in 2013, working for boutiques and divings.\nShe started working in yachting in 2021 on yacht Floki as stewardess. In 2023 she moved to yacht North Wind.\nHobbies/ Interests: Scuba diving, cycling, travel, gourd carving."},{"name":"Yunus Kesgin","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::7819143053::vessel::77945888-486c-11ee-a45f-fdfff6163a60::assets::bd9e5670-295e-11ef-bff7-9d94981faba8.jpeg/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"Birth: 14.11.1998 in Muğla\nEducation: Istanbul Maltepe Commercial Vocational High School\nPrevious Work Experiences in Brief:\n2013-2017 Yacht Baba Veli 7 Commercial -Deckhand\n2017-2021 Sailing Yacht Dali (Private) - Deckhand\n2021-2024 North Wind Commercial Yacht – Shipyard and Deckhand\nHobbies/ Interests: Table tennis, sailing, water sports"},{"name":"Mine Isiklar","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::7819143053::vessel::77945888-486c-11ee-a45f-fdfff6163a60::assets::e927a990-295e-11ef-bff7-9d94981faba8.jpeg/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"Mine was born in Instanbul in 1982.\nEducation:\n2001-2008: Marmara University/Radio, TV and Cinema;\n2008: Harvard University/Summer School ESL;\n2008-2009: City College of Marin County/Production Leadership;\n2009-2010: US Berkeley Extension/Marketing;\n2019-2020: City College of San Francisco/Production Planning\nShe entered Marmara University's Radio, Cinema, and Television Department in 2001. She worked as an assistant director and post production manager in TV series and f ilms. Transitioning to the music industry in 2005, she served as the production manager for the Athena band for three years. In 2008, she went to San Francisco to further her education, completing marketing certificate programs at the College of Marin Coun ty and UC Berkeley. During her time there, she participated in intellectually enriching events such as the San Francisco Film Festival and the Los Angeles Book Fair with Winslow Event Company. Returning to Turkey in 2010, she continued her career as an age ncy producer in creative advertising agencies (TBWA, Teamred). Over time, she discovered her interest in the kitchen alongside event planning. While studying production planning at San Francisco College in 2017, she also received training in kitchen cultur e at the Vegan Culinary Academy. During this period, she honed her skills in service, wine, and hosting by working in restaurants of various cultures. Her journey led her to discover yacht tourism during her time working in San Francisco Marina, where she began working as a hostess on commercial motor yachts. Now, she continues her career as a hostess on the North Wind, utilizing all the experiences she has gained along the way."},{"name":"Gozde Sen Tanak","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::7819143053::vessel::77945888-486c-11ee-a45f-fdfff6163a60::assets::810d7730-295f-11ef-b2e5-c5e14ecf6a1b.jpeg/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"Gozde was born in Kocaeli in 1988.\nEducation: 2009-2013 Kyrenia American University/Public Relations. 2014-2016 2016: Usak University/Thesis Based Graduate Program in Public Relations and Advertising."},{"name":"Suleyman Can","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::7819143053::vessel::77945888-486c-11ee-a45f-fdfff6163a60::assets::a5a17ab0-295f-11ef-b2e5-c5e14ecf6a1b.jpeg/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"Suleyman was born in Fethiye in 1999.\nEducation: 2014-2018: Mustafa Kemal Vocational and Technical Anatolian High.\nPrevious yacht experiences:\n2015 Gulet Reina\n2016-2017 Gulet Okoto\n2017-2020 Gulet Luce del Mare\n2020-2022 MY Cinar Yildizi\n2022- North Wind"},{"name":"Orcin Uysal","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::7819143053::vessel::77945888-486c-11ee-a45f-fdfff6163a60::assets::c70e2680-295f-11ef-b2e5-c5e14ecf6a1b.jpeg/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"Orcin was born in Fethiye in 1998.\nEducation: 2012 2016: Fethi ye Anatolian Tourism and Hotel Management High School.\nExperiences:\n2019-2020 2020: Barut Hotel Fethiye;\n2021 Yacht Seyhan\n2021-2023 Yacht Alegria"}],"pricing":{"weekPricingFrom":{"currency":"EUR","price":7350000,"displayCurrency":"EUR","displayPrice":7350000,"unit":"WEEK"},"weekPricingTo":{"currency":"EUR","price":9625000,"displayCurrency":"EUR","displayPrice":9625000,"unit":"WEEK"},"pricingInfo":[{"name":"July and August","effectiveDates":[{"from":"2025-07-01T00:00:00.000Z","to":"2025-08-31T23:59:59.999Z"},{"from":"2026-07-01T00:00:00.000Z","to":"2026-08-31T23:59:59.999Z"},{"from":"2027-07-01T00